Jethro Ibileke/Benin Edo State Government has disclosed that it would spend no less than N35 million to improve infrastructure and boost facilities at the State Sickle Cell Center. The State Commissioner for Health, Dr. David Osifo, made this disclosure Thursday, while commissioning laboratory equipment donated to the State Sickle Cell Board, by the PRESCO Plc/University of Benin Teaching Hospital (UBTH) Sickle Cell Awareness Golf Tournament Fund Management Committee. Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from The NEWS. Click here to read the full text on the original website.